# Vercel Speed Insights Configuration Report

## Summary
Vercel Speed Insights is **already fully installed and configured** in this project. No changes were necessary.

## Current Configuration

### 1. Package Installation ✅
- Package: `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0`
- Location: `frontend/package.json` dependencies
- Status: Installed and up-to-date

### 2. Integration ✅
- Framework: Next.js 16.1.6 (App Router)
- Implementation: `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx`
- Import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
- Component: `<SpeedInsights />` added to the root layout's body section

### 3. Implementation Details
The SpeedInsights component is correctly placed in the root layout file following Vercel's official documentation for Next.js App Router:

```tsx
export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" data-theme="light">
      <body>
        {/* Theme and Auth Providers */}
        <ThemeProvider>
          <AuthProvider>{children}</AuthProvider>
        </ThemeProvider>
        <SpeedInsights />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This placement ensures Speed Insights tracking is available across all pages in the application.

